      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-02-16T17:29:49.720Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Ok I just testedI have Garmin Pro strap&gt;Forerunner 655 (same as Fenix 6 I think)\u2026   For sure forerunner is connect in TD app and not garmin strap directly.</p>\n<p>I was just walking around the house doing some stuff for 30 minutes and see no problem.<br>\n,<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6_2_475x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"bvvr8yfHXVsBmTbKzv26HhAdb5c\" width=\"475\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6_2_475x500.jpeg, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6_2_712x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/5/50a7ac90e963082c3dd88a3c627e4cb885c128e6_2_950x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"393B60\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1484\u00d71562 207 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>One thing I did notice is if my phone was not against my body (wrist or even clothes), it would stop showing my HR on the watch (see above).</p>\n<p>Strangely against a chair nothing but putting against my shorts it would show my HR on the watch\u2026 but still it kept working in our app the whole time.</p>\n<p>EDIT: Oh this was version 5.1.7 of our app, now trying 5.1.8 (latest)</p>\n<p>EDIT2: Ok tried 5.1.8 also no issue.</p>",
