      "id": 71459,
      "name": "",
      "username": "icruces",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/e5b9ba/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-02-17T12:10:54.060Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Thanks for testing. For me it takes less than 10 minutes to happen.</p>\n<p>I will give more context about my workflow:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I open TrainerDay (TD) and wait until it connects to Kickr Bike sensors</li>\n<li>I start a \u201cBike Indoor\u201d activity in my Fenix 6, which also connects to Kickr Bike sensors.</li>\n<li>I start the HR broadcasting in the watch and wait until TD detects it.</li>\n<li>I go back to the Bike Indoor screen in the watch and I start the workout.</li>\n<li>At some point, the HR in TD gets stuck and I need to go back to the broadcasting screen in the watch and stop/start it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I have followed similar steps with the Wahoo app without issues (but tbh I have only used it a couple of times so maybe I was lucky).</p>\n<p>Also, I have been using TD since 2022 and I don\u2019t recall this happening at the beginning, I would say it has been happening since one year ago or so.</p>",
